  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    Collects
    Should be used on Generators that require other models.
    Generates
    All generators need to be annotated with this or Collects to be used with Knit.
    Inputs
    All inputters need to be annotated with this to be scanned by KnitProcessor and get registered into a Model Manager.
    KnitView
    All views such as Activities and Fragments need to be tagged with this to be registered with Knit.
    Model
    All KnitModels need to be annotated with this to be scanned and registered with Knit.
    ModelEvent
    Methods that listen to events fired from Models need to be annotated with these.
    Presenter
    All Knit Presenters need to be tagged with this to be scanned and registered with Knit.
    Use
    Internal Use.
    UseMethod
    Internal Use.
    ViewEvent
    Methods that listen to events fired from Views need to be annotated with these.
